    <item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-ietf-ace-pubsub-profile-04.txt'>
        <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-ietf-ace-pubsub-profile-04.txt</link>
        <title>"Pub-Sub Profile for Authentication and Authorization for Constrained Environments (ACE)", Francesca Palombini, Cigdem Sengul</title>
        <dc:date>2021-12-29T23:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
        <description>This specification defines an application profile for authentication and authorization for Publishers and Subscribers in a constrained pub-sub scenario, using the ACE framework.  This profile relies on transport layer or application layer security to authorize the pub- sub clients to the broker.  Moreover, it describes the use of application layer security to protect the content of the pub-sub client message exchange through the broker.  The profile covers pub- sub scenarios using either the Constrained Application Protocol (CoAP) [I-D.ietf-core-coap-pubsub] or the Message Queue Telemetry Transport (MQTT) [MQTT-OASIS-Standard-v5] protocol.</description>
    </item>
